China is creating a 'great wall of sand' in the South China Sea, US Navy claims .
It is 1.5 square miles (four square kilometres) in size and was created by dumping sand on live coral reefs, possibly damaging local ecosystems .
Experts have told MailOnline that the activities could be hugely damaging to coral reefs .
China is using dredging vessels to dig up sediment from the sea, and then dumping it on subermeged coral reefs to make islands .